Gombe State governor, Alhaji Muhammadu Inuwa Yahaya, has commiserated with his Adamawa State counterpart, Governor Umaru Fintiri over the demise of his mother, Hajiya Fatima Umaru  Badami, who died in Yola. In a condolence message, Governor Yahaya described the death of Hajiya Fatima as a great loss not only to her immediate family but to entire Adamawa state and Nigeria. A statement by Ismaila Uba Misilli, his senior special assistant on media and publicity quoted the governor as saying the late Hajiya Fatima was an upright woman and family pillar, who lived a fruitful life and impacted positively on the lives of her children and community. He said although Hajiya Fatima died at a time her elderly and motherly counsel and wisdom were needed by her children, especially Governor Fintiri, “We must take solace in the fact that she left behind a lasting legacy through her children and exemplary life which will  continue to be cherished.” Governor Yahaya extended his heartfelt condolences to Governor Fintiri and members of his family as well as the Government and people of Adamawa state over the great loss, praying Almighty Allah to grant the deceased Aljannat Firdaus. Similarly, Governor Yahaya said he received with sadness, the news of the death of Alhaji Adamu Danjarida (Madakin Kwami) who died yesterday at the age of 78 years. In a condolence message,  the governor described the late chairman of the PDP Elders’ Forum as a great loss not only to his immediate family but the state and the nation as a whole. He described Alhaji Danjarida as a grassroots politician and great community leader who impacted on the lives of many. 